<h2>Introduction</h2>
<p>The file explorer is a component available on all operating systems. When it is present in a web page, it should behave as expected by the user.</p>

<h2>Navigation mode</h2>

<p>Using the mouse, each file can be opened via a double click. The <kbd>ctrl</kbd> and <kbd>shift</kbd> keys allow multiple selection.</p>
<p>Using the keyboard, the arrow keys the move the selection. Pressing enter allows to open a file. The <kbd>control+spacebar</kbd> or <kbd>shift+arrow</kbd> shortcuts to select multiple files.</p>
<p>Using a screen reader is the same as the keyboard, each file is correctly vocalized (name, size, type, ...); in addition it vocalizes the state of the file (selected/unselected).</p>

